"I ask for the forgiveness of the Korean people for past illegal wiretapping," National Intelligence Service chief Kim Seung-kew said, reading a statement to reporters.
Hong had assumed his duties in Washington in February.
News of the resignation came on the same day that six-nation talks in Beijing, aimed at getting North Korea to give up its nuclear weapons program, resumed after a 13-month hiatus.
